#  Online Retail Sales Analysis (SQL Project)

##  Project Overview

This project focuses on designing a relational database for an online retail store and analyzing sales data using SQL queries. The goal is to extract meaningful business insights such as top-selling products, customer value, and revenue trends.

---

##  Objectives

* Design a relational database for an online store
* Store customer, product, and order data
* Perform data analysis using SQL queries
* Generate insights to support business decisions

---

##  Database Schema

### 1. Customers

* customer_id (Primary Key)
* name
* city

### 2. Products

* product_id (Primary Key)
* name
* category
* price

### 3. Orders

* order_id (Primary Key)
* customer_id (Foreign Key)
* order_date

### 4. Order_Items

* order_id (Foreign Key)
* product_id (Foreign Key)
* quantity

---

## 🔗 Relationships

* Customers → Orders (One-to-Many)
* Orders → Order_Items (One-to-Many)
* Products → Order_Items (One-to-Many)

---

##  Features / Queries Implemented

### 1. Top-Selling Products

Identifies products with the highest total quantity sold.

### 2. Most Valuable Customers

Finds customers who have spent the most money.

### 3. Monthly Revenue

Calculates total revenue generated each month.

### 4. Category-wise Sales Analysis

Analyzes total sales for each product category.

### 5. Inactive Customers

Detects customers who have not placed any orders.

---

##  Technologies Used

* SQL (MySQL)
* MySQL Workbench

---

##  Sample Insights

* Identify which products are most popular
* Understand customer purchasing behavior
* Track revenue trends over time
* Analyze category performance
* Detect inactive customers

---

##  Outcome

This project demonstrates how SQL can be used to transform raw retail data into actionable business insights, helping improve decision-making and sales strategies.

